Describe a period of time from your studies that was the most difficult for you

I would like to talk about the most challenging period I experienced during my studies. It happened when I was in my last year of high school and was preparing for the national university entrance exam.

The primary reason why it was tough because of the heavy load of knowledge that I had to absord during a short period. The final result would determine the university and major that I would be admitted to. As you can see, It had a huge impact on shaping my future career prospects. In addition to that, there were countless students competing for a limited spots in high-ranked (prestigious) universitys. So, the competition was extremely intense. Moreover, there were also expectations of having a good performance from my family. These factors were attributed to the high level of stress associated with this exam.

During that time, I dedicated long hours to self-study in evenings and weekends while attending school during daytime. I only focused on revising the subjects that contributed significantly to my final score. To accelerate my preparing process, I applied various strategies such as forming study groups with my classmates and asking for guidance from my teachers. I also practiced past exam papers to become familiar with the exam structures.

To my mind, it was a laborious experience. There were many times I had to stay up late until 1 am to complete assignments.
But my hard work eventually paid off and I got accepted to my desired university and got the chance to pursue my desired major. When I look back, I'm extremely grateful for that experience, It taught me a lot of lessons about collaborating with other individuals to gain better outcomes, and being willing to ask for directions when I feel lost. Those valuable skills have continued to help me throughout my academic journey.

