With the support of technological tools such as tablets and educational apps, lessons can become far more interactive and stimulating. For example, students can participate in online quizzes, education games, and virtual simulations, which not only enhance their cognitive skills but also foster healthy competition and collaboration. In my opinion, when used approriately, technology can significantly improve both students' motivation and learning outcomes.

Do you think computers will one day replace teachers in the classroom
In my opinion, it's very unlikely for technology to replace teachers. It's admitted that digitalization in classrooms has brought about numerous benefits for learners, but the human element in education remains irreplaceable. Firstly, teachers bring a wealth of knowledge and expertise that comes from years of practical experience. They possess the ability to adapt teaching methods to cater to individual learners' needs. Secondly, as human beings, students always desire for emotional connections. And teachers are avaiable to provide mental support when students are in need. In conclusion, technology should be viewed as an augumentation rather than a complete replacement for teachers.

